# Workflow Runs

Monitor, trigger, and manage the execution of GitHub Actions workflows.

## gh CLI

```bash
# List recent runs
gh run list
gh run list --workflow ci.yml
gh run list --status failure --limit 10
gh run list --branch main --json status,conclusion,name,databaseId

# View a specific run
gh run view 12345
gh run view 12345 --log
gh run view 12345 --json status,conclusion,jobs

# View failed job logs
gh run view 12345 --log-failed

# Watch a run in real-time
gh run watch 12345
gh run watch  # watch the most recent run

# Trigger a workflow dispatch
gh workflow run deploy.yml -f environment=production -f version=1.2.3
gh workflow run ci.yml --ref develop

# Re-run failed jobs
gh run rerun 12345 --failed

# Re-run all jobs
gh run rerun 12345

# Cancel a run
gh run cancel 12345

# Download logs
gh run view 12345 --log > run.log
```

## REST API

```javascript
import { Octokit } from "@octokit/rest";
const octokit = new Octokit({ auth: process.env.GITHUB_TOKEN });

// List workflow runs
const { data: runs } = await octokit.actions.listWorkflowRuns({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  workflow_id: "ci.yml",
  status: "completed",
  per_page: 10,
});
runs.workflow_runs.forEach(r => {
  console.log(r.id, r.status, r.conclusion, r.html_url);
});

// Get a specific run
const { data: run } = await octokit.actions.getWorkflowRun({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  run_id: 12345,
});
console.log(run.status, run.conclusion, run.head_sha);

// List jobs for a run
const { data: jobs } = await octokit.actions.listJobsForWorkflowRun({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  run_id: 12345,
});
jobs.jobs.forEach(j => {
  console.log(j.name, j.status, j.conclusion);
  j.steps.forEach(s => console.log(`  ${s.name}: ${s.conclusion}`));
});

// Trigger workflow dispatch
await octokit.actions.createWorkflowDispatch({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  workflow_id: "deploy.yml",
  ref: "main",
  inputs: { environment: "production", version: "1.2.3" },
});

// Re-run failed jobs
await octokit.actions.reRunWorkflowFailedJobs({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  run_id: 12345,
});

// Cancel a run
await octokit.actions.cancelWorkflowRun({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  run_id: 12345,
});

// Download run logs
const { data: logs } = await octokit.actions.downloadWorkflowRunLogs({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  run_id: 12345,
});
// Returns a redirect URL to a zip archive of logs
```

## Run Status and Conclusion

| Field | Values | Meaning |
|-------|--------|---------|
| `status` | `queued`, `in_progress`, `completed` | Current execution state |
| `conclusion` | `success`, `failure`, `cancelled`, `skipped`, `timed_out`, `action_required` | Final result (only when completed) |

## Polling for Completion

```bash
# Watch until completion (blocks until done)
gh run watch 12345 --exit-status
# Exit code 0 if success, non-zero if failure

# Poll via API
while true; do
  STATUS=$(gh run view 12345 --json status --jq '.status')
  if [ "$STATUS" = "completed" ]; then
    CONCLUSION=$(gh run view 12345 --json conclusion --jq '.conclusion')
    echo "Run completed: $CONCLUSION"
    break
  fi
  sleep 10
done
```
